1
00:00:00,710 --> 00:00:02,010
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,680
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:05,410
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,250 --> 00:00:08,680
(Episode 33)

5
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:10,980
Kim Myung Hui?

6
00:00:41,110 --> 00:00:42,650
What's going on here?

7
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:50,860
Right now,

8
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:54,030
I can't give up
on avenging my sister,

9
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:58,000
but I can't take down
Park Tae Ho either.

10
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,760
But one day,

11
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:03,800
when the time is right,

12
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:06,400
I'll reveal the whole truth.

13
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,940
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

14
00:01:08,540 --> 00:01:10,340
I will clear your name...

15
00:01:11,410 --> 00:01:13,310
and see to it
that Park Tae Ho is punished.

16
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:17,880
Even if it costs me...

17
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:20,890
everything I have,

18
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:24,890
I swear I will keep my promise.

19
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:32,230
I wanted to show you
how I really feel, sir.

20
00:01:33,930 --> 00:01:34,930
How you feel?

21
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,840
If you want to know how I feel,

22
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:44,240
give me the gallery.

23
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:47,410
The gallery?

24
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:53,990
You suddenly want to show me
how you feel...

25
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,790
and ask for the gallery
out of nowhere?

26
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,290
Start by explaining yourself.

27
00:02:02,990 --> 00:02:05,630
I heard you removed Ms. Oh
as gallery director...

28
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:08,570
and were desperately looking for me.

29
00:02:10,370 --> 00:02:13,570
You punished her on my behalf
for what she did to me.

30
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,610
It's only right
that I show my gratitude.

31
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:23,650
Since I'm the reason
the gallery is without a director,

32
00:02:24,950 --> 00:02:26,420
I'd like to help...

33
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,290
as Ms. Oh's replacement.

34
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:35,630
You want to help me
in Oh Jung Ran's place?

35
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:37,560
Before we get to that,

36
00:02:38,730 --> 00:02:43,300
I need to hear what happened
between you and Jung Ran first.

37
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,240
Just like last time,

38
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:55,580
she grilled me,
bringing up Eunhwa Trading again.

39
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,150
Then,

40
00:02:58,620 --> 00:03:00,850
she even told me to drop dead.

41
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:06,690
It brought back memories
of how she almost killed me.

42
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,230
Even though it was 30 years ago,

43
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,100
I was so terrified and distraught...

44
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:16,670
that I couldn't even go home...

45
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,340
and had to run away.

46
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,640
I see.

47
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:28,680
A near-death experience
isn't easily forgotten.

48
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,220
You must've been really shaken up.

49
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:36,890
Did any other memories come back?

50
00:03:40,790 --> 00:03:42,130
The memory of that day 30 years ago,

51
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,930
when I first joined
the Adele family,

52
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:46,800
is much clearer now.

53
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,770
Both then and now,

54
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:56,470
I realize you're the only one
who can protect me, sir.

55
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:58,010
That's why...

56
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:01,810
I want to be useful to you.

57
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:14,130
Don't keep me at arm's length.

58
00:04:15,530 --> 00:04:17,260
Let me into your inner circle.

59
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:26,570
In place of Ms. Oh,
please put your trust in me.

60
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:33,310
I need to step in as your accomplice
in place of Oh Jung Ran.

61
00:04:34,550 --> 00:04:36,710
I'll be the witness to your sins,

62
00:04:37,650 --> 00:04:38,880
the proof of your guilt,

63
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,490
and the one who reports your crimes.

64
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:46,560
(Adele)

65
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,670
Fine. Do whatever you want.

66
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:57,340
Let's...

67
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,570
get married.

68
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:02,740
What she wants?

69
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:07,080
Does that mean
Chloe wants to marry him?

70
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,620
Things are finally starting
to add up.

71
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:17,790
Who knew Chloe and Hyun Jun
were involved like that?

72
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:22,790
That Chloe really has a way
of wrapping men around her finger.

73
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:24,130
Get out.

74
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:29,930
Why are you so worked up...

75
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:31,540
when you and Chloe
were never even a thing?

76
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:35,970
You were only drawn to her
because she looked like the late Jin Ju.

77
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,480
Yes, you're right.

78
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:43,410
After Jin Ju died,
I was numb for seven years.

79
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:47,520
But what she said got to me,
and I started worrying about her.

80
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,690
For the first time in seven years,
I could breathe again.

81
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,330
It made me want
to truly start living again.

82
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:59,230
What mattered more
than her resemblance to Jin Ju...

83
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:01,700
or the thought
that she could be Jin Ju...

84
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,700
was her goodness...

85
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:07,110
and who she truly is.

86
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:09,640
That's what I realized.

87
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:12,610
Are you really...

88
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,680
confessing...

89
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:18,920
your love for Chloe
right in front of me?

90
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:21,550
Yes.

91
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:24,790
If what I'm feeling is love,
then yes, I am.

92
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,490
Park Min Jun.

93
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,230
How could you?

94
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,870
Drop those pathetic feelings
right now.

95
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,610
You saw it yourself.

96
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:45,310
Chloe promised to marry Hyun Jun.

97
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:46,540
She chose him,

98
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:49,310
not you.

99
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:54,050
What you're feeling isn't love.

100
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,050
It's just a dirty,

101
00:06:57,790 --> 00:06:59,490
disgusting obsession.

102
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:25,320
He suspects who I really am,
and he still wants to get married?

103
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:29,750
Does he know I'm Baek Jin Ju or not?

104
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:34,730
What was that all about?

105
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,760
Is this because of me?

106
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,070
Are you running away because
my feelings make you uncomfortable?

107
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,640
Is this your response to how I feel?

108
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,810
Did Min Jun actually confess...

109
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:56,150
his feelings to her?

110
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:02,120
I thought you were waiting
for my answer.

111
00:08:02,890 --> 00:08:05,920
You proposed to me, and I said yes.

112
00:08:06,690 --> 00:08:07,930
But you don't look happy.

113
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:10,700
You said you didn't want
to be used by me.

114
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,760
So why the sudden change of heart?

115
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:18,300
Something you said...

116
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,270
kept urging me on.

117
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:24,840
You said that at least...

118
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,010
I'd have you by my side.

119
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:32,520
And if I can have that,
nothing else matters.

120
00:08:34,290 --> 00:08:35,450
That's what I've decided.

121
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:39,490
I chose to ignore who you are
and how cowardly...

122
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,360
that makes me.

123
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:44,160
But let me ask you one thing. Why?

124
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:49,600
Why me and not Min Jun?

125
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:56,340
Because...

126
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,110
Because I'm Chloe.

127
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:04,380
When everyone else saw me
as Baek Jin Ju,

128
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,650
you saw me as Chloe.

129
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:10,220
I'm choosing the person...

130
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,760
who will always see me as Chloe,
no matter what.

131
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,430
So I'm not supposed to suspect
you're Jin Ju?

132
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:18,700
And even if I already know,

133
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:21,630
I'm not supposed to say anything?

134
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:26,070
Is that the only way
I can keep you with me?

135
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,710
I can't trust you completely.

136
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:31,810
For all I know,

137
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:34,880
you might've figured out
that I'm Baek Jin Ju.

138
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:37,210
But right now,

139
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:40,750
I have to use you,
even if it's like this.

140
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,440
You stayed out all night,

141
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:03,640
and now you're wearing
bright red lipstick?

142
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:07,140
Did you find a man overnight
or something?

143
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:10,410
What kind of nonsense
are you talking about?

144
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,780
Stop making a scene
and go back to the annex.

145
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:15,890
Why are you getting worked up?

146
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:20,120
I was just asking
because her lips are so ridiculously red.

147
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:26,930
When a woman starts wearing
lipstick that red,

148
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,630
it's usually because of a new man.

149
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:31,870
I don't have a new man.

150
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:33,940
I just had a change of heart.

151
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:38,740
I've made a decision
to show more gratitude...

152
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,310
and serve...

153
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:42,510
the chairman better.

154
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:47,050
What? Show him more gratitude
and serve him better?

155
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:51,560
That's right.

156
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,760
Go on in and get some rest.

157
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:57,660
As for the gallery,
let's give it some more thought.

158
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:00,770
The gallery? What's that about?

159
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:02,000
Drop it.

160
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,040
You...

161
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,450
You. What game are you playing?

162
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,880
You're Kim Myung Hui.

163
00:11:18,980 --> 00:11:21,550
The pure and noble Kim Myung Hui.

164
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:24,720
Are you really siding
with Park Tae Ho, a murderer?

165
00:11:25,290 --> 00:11:28,060
Instead of being horrified,
you're flirting with him?

166
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:31,560
And what's all this
about the gallery?

167
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,200
You ask way too many questions.

168
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,270
You're the one
who told me his secret.

169
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,770
Are you getting nervous now?

170
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:46,880
That day,

171
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:53,050
the pure, noble Kim Myung Hui died.

172
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,150
But...

173
00:11:57,490 --> 00:11:59,720
even if you could kill
Kim Myung Hui,

174
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:02,130
you can't break me.

175
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,300
Like you said,

176
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,230
after wanting Adele for 30 years,

177
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,870
how could I possibly give it up?

178
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:13,540
Instead of living in misery,

179
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:15,340
I'm going to take what I want.

180
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:20,210
I'll keep getting closer
to the chairman...

181
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:22,510
and take whatever I can.

182
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:27,790
First, I'll start
with the gallery you lost.

183
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:29,790
You...

184
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:33,020
Have you lost her mind?

185
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:39,530
If you want to stop me,
go tell him right now.

186
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:43,770
That Park Tae Ho is a murderer.

187
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:47,840
Tell him...

188
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:50,410
you told me yourself.

189
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:54,510
Then we'll see what happens.

190
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,820
It'll be fun, won't it?

191
00:13:12,130 --> 00:13:14,400
You couldn't pour some for yourself?

192
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:18,970
What's wrong?
What's eating you up like this?

193
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,110
Did Chairman Park
bite your head off again?

194
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:25,980
It's not him. It's Kim Myung Hui.

195
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:29,350
Something's not right.
She's a completely different person.

196
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:32,620
She wasn't like that,
even when she first moved in.

197
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:35,020
That's what you get
for telling her everything.

198
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:38,090
Did she snap...

199
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:40,190
and say she'd punish Chairman Park?

200
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:42,160
At least that'd make sense.

201
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:45,260
I expected her to either snap
and challenge Tae Ho...

202
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,700
or go mad from the misery
the truth brought her.

203
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:49,530
It should've been one of those two.

204
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,040
But she's completely unfazed.

205
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,400
If anything, she's more shameless.

206
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,570
That's absurd.

207
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:58,880
No one changes that drastically
overnight.

208
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,580
You had to have seen it
with your own eyes.

209
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:04,680
Wait.

210
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:07,550
Kim Myung Hui couldn't have changed.

211
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:10,290
She can only be pretending.

212
00:14:12,890 --> 00:14:15,230
She's playing a very dangerous game.

213
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,030
It's like she became...

214
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,170
a completely different person
overnight.

215
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:26,770
And now she wants me
to put her in charge of the gallery?

216
00:14:28,710 --> 00:14:31,180
She's openly trying
to cross the line.

217
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:37,250
Is she trying to take down Jung Ran
and replace her,

218
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,380
or, like everything else,

219
00:14:40,950 --> 00:14:43,520
is she looking for leverage over me?

220
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:48,390
What the...

221
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,930
So you're just going
to openly defy me now?

222
00:14:51,330 --> 00:14:52,730
Get back to the annex!

223
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,000
You can't let Kim Myung Hui
fool you.

224
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:58,670
If you put her in charge
of the gallery, you'll be at risk.

225
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,140
You'll regret it.

226
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:03,310
How would that put me at risk?

227
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,580
Well...

228
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:10,480
Stop trying to think of an excuse
and just answer me.

229
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:13,650
Something happened at the gallery,
didn't it?

230
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,220
It's not that anything happened.

231
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:19,360
It's that Kim Myung Hui has changed.

232
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:22,290
That lipstick shows
she's up to something.

233
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:26,430
Whatever you do, don't leave her
in charge of the gallery.

234
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:30,230
The exhibition
and your upcoming deal...

235
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:31,600
could be at risk.

236
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:34,840
You were the one bragging that
no one else could do what you do.

237
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,670
Are you making a scene because...

238
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:37,910
you feel threatened
by her taking over?

239
00:15:38,810 --> 00:15:41,110
It's too late to beg now.

240
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,780
Honey, wait.

241
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:48,390
Fine. You'll learn the hard way.

242
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:50,290
Don't say I didn't warn you.

243
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:52,090
You're the one who threw this away!

244
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:01,670
From now on, I'm neither Kim Dan Hui
nor Kim Myung Hui.

245
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:04,200
I have to become a monster
like Oh Jung Ran...

246
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:06,940
and a devil like Park Tae Ho.

247
00:16:27,060 --> 00:16:28,060
It's me.

248
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:30,930
It's about tomorrow's deal
at the gallery.

249
00:16:31,430 --> 00:16:33,800
Bring me the item and the paperwork.

250
00:16:34,730 --> 00:16:36,000
Kim Myung Hui...

251
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:40,000
I need to test her
and see what she's really after.

252
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:42,110
Right.

253
00:17:00,790 --> 00:17:02,890
How did you get in here?

254
00:17:04,330 --> 00:17:06,500
My feelings for you were real.

255
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:12,200
I genuinely wanted to be with you
and build a different life.

256
00:17:14,570 --> 00:17:16,240
Were you playing me from the start,

257
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,840
like this was all part of some plan?

258
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:20,940
What are you really after?

259
00:17:21,350 --> 00:17:22,350
No, wait.

260
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,220
Why do you want to get married?

261
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:28,890
Who the heck are you?

262
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:33,560
Who are you? Tell me!
Just who are you?

263
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:38,000
Who are you?

264
00:17:49,570 --> 00:17:50,610
That's why...

265
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:53,610
I told you to stay in the past.

266
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:00,620
If you had just held on
to Baek Jin Ju,

267
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:04,350
you wouldn't be this heartbroken.

268
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:12,930
This is on you
for letting Chloe get to you.

269
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:16,330
Even if you come to me looking hurt,

270
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:21,440
even if you resent and hate me,

271
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,440
I...

272
00:18:28,610 --> 00:18:29,610
I...

273
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:38,620
(Park Min Jun,
Adele's Head of Division 1)

274
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:41,160
(Adele)

275
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:47,660
This wedding...

276
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:53,400
Was Chloe really the one
who wanted it first?

277
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,640
Yes.

278
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:00,110
She was the one who proposed.

279
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:06,250
Why?

280
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,260
Other than the fact
that we love each other,

281
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,460
what other reason do we need?

282
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,800
So Chloe...

283
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:24,200
- really loves you?
- Yes!

284
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:29,070
Chloe's heart belongs to me,

285
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,080
so stay out of it.

286
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:53,030
A friend who was like a brother.

287
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,730
A brother who was like a friend.

288
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,310
That's all over now.

289
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:07,380
Why do you still look so down?

290
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:11,080
I already proved
I wouldn't get in the way...

291
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:12,820
of your wedding.

292
00:20:13,150 --> 00:20:15,990
In fact, I even went along
with your lie...

293
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:18,460
when you made it seem
like I was helping you...

294
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:20,560
instead of just staying out of it.

295
00:20:21,390 --> 00:20:22,790
Who says it's a lie?

296
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,930
Helping me take on the chairman
goes without saying.

297
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:31,300
But you have to help
with my wedding too.

298
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,470
That's my condition.

299
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:35,370
You can't even get married
without help?

300
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:43,850
You're the one who told me
to think about what I stand to gain.

301
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:48,650
Once this deal is done,
you get the bio division.

302
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:51,190
But what do I walk away with?

303
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:55,660
You get to keep your life.

304
00:20:56,390 --> 00:20:57,930
That's not enough for me.

305
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:02,800
I need to get something
out of this too.

306
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:08,340
Fine. Have your precious wedding.

307
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:13,410
My wedding comes first.
No exceptions.

308
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:14,950
After I get married,

309
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:16,980
we'll use the leverage I have
on the chairman,

310
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:19,780
and I'll help you secure
the bio division you want...

311
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,720
for a steal.

312
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:27,220
Right, what good are the terms
of a deal anyway?

313
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:31,060
As long as I can use you
and put you in harm's way,

314
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:32,560
I don't care.

315
00:21:32,930 --> 00:21:36,170
After all, I'm going to ruin
that marriage anyway.

316
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,500
To get Min Jun to give up on you,

317
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:40,940
I need you to help...

318
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,710
make my marriage happen.

319
00:21:43,570 --> 00:21:45,380
And after I'm done using you...

320
00:21:45,380 --> 00:21:46,580
The bio division, was it?

321
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:48,080
Don't make me laugh.

322
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:52,220
I'm going to use the chairman
to get rid of you for good.

323
00:22:03,260 --> 00:22:04,260
Open it.

324
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:15,910
The gallery is hosting
an exhibition soon.

325
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,840
We'll showcase private collections
from political and business leaders.

326
00:22:21,650 --> 00:22:22,650
This is one of the pieces.

327
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:24,510
The gems in this piece
are so rare...

328
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:28,120
they were once reserved
for the royal family,

329
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,790
so it's now being considered
for cultural asset status.

330
00:22:31,490 --> 00:22:32,490
A cultural asset?

331
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:35,390
Yes, and of course, the gems...

332
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:37,930
are all authentic.

333
00:22:43,370 --> 00:22:45,500
(World Gemological Institute)

334
00:22:45,670 --> 00:22:48,940
I see the gems were appraised
by a foreign institution.

335
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:51,610
I thought
getting it appraised locally...

336
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:52,610
might cause rumors.

337
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:56,380
The owner is a politician,

338
00:22:56,380 --> 00:22:59,820
so he can't easily avoid questions
about it becoming a cultural asset.

339
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:05,620
But if he lets it be designated,
he can't sell it off.

340
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,960
And yet,

341
00:23:08,890 --> 00:23:11,160
it's now being considered
for cultural asset designation,

342
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:14,330
so he came to me for help.

343
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:18,100
He's trying to avoid it
being designated a cultural asset?

344
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,440
That's right.

345
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:22,810
All you have to do,

346
00:23:23,470 --> 00:23:26,110
is sign this appraisal report.

347
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:32,650
An appraisal report?

348
00:23:33,950 --> 00:23:37,220
Soon, there will be reports
that the gems are fake,

349
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:39,060
and the owner will say...

350
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:41,360
the results came from you,

351
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:43,590
an internationally certified
gemologist...

352
00:23:44,930 --> 00:23:47,100
at our very own AD Appraisals.

353
00:23:48,630 --> 00:23:52,370
So under my name,
a real piece will become a fake.

354
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,010
There's no need to worry.

355
00:23:56,540 --> 00:23:58,780
Everything's already been arranged.

356
00:24:00,010 --> 00:24:01,950
We'll wrap this up
without any further appraisals.

357
00:24:05,580 --> 00:24:08,690
(AD Appraisals:
Gemstone Appraisal Report)

358
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:13,390
I considered another appraiser,
but I decided to give this to you.

359
00:24:14,860 --> 00:24:17,560
You said you'd replace Jung Ran,
help me with my work,

360
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,800
and that you were ready
to cross the line.

361
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,400
You can handle this, right?

362
00:24:32,210 --> 00:24:36,010
Can you really go against
your principles as a gemologist?

363
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:39,250
Can you abandon who you are...

364
00:24:39,820 --> 00:24:41,690
and cross that line to my side?

365
00:24:43,450 --> 00:24:44,690
This is hardly a difficult task.

366
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:48,660
You're really going to do it?

367
00:24:49,490 --> 00:24:52,560
You entrusted this to me,
so of course I'll handle it.

368
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:59,700
This is a plan to test me
and put pressure on me at the same time.

369
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:02,840
He still doesn't trust me.

370
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:12,650
You're passing off something real
as a fake.

371
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:15,650
If anything goes wrong,
your career as a gemologist is over.

372
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:18,920
You worked so hard
to build your reputation as one.

373
00:25:19,490 --> 00:25:23,160
If you lose your seat as president,
you'll have nothing left.

374
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:24,790
I know.

375
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,230
Chairman Park knows that,

376
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,370
which is why
he's testing me this way.

377
00:25:29,870 --> 00:25:31,070
Is it really necessary...

378
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,000
to do something
so dirty and dangerous?

379
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:43,810
Chloe.

380
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:54,960
If only you were Baek Jin Ju.

381
00:25:56,630 --> 00:25:58,190
If she had survived,

382
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,130
I wouldn't feel
this completely devastated.

383
00:26:05,070 --> 00:26:06,270
Why are you looking at me like that?

384
00:26:07,970 --> 00:26:10,840
Can we talk for a moment?

385
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:12,710
Sorry?

386
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:23,520
When you're feeling frustrated,
there's no place quite like this.

387
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:33,760
You haven't asked what's on my mind.

388
00:26:36,370 --> 00:26:39,070
I'm not a big fan of that question.

389
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:42,270
It's too easy for the one who asks,

390
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:44,610
but it's hard for the one
who has to answer.

391
00:26:46,210 --> 00:26:49,350
I don't like to pry
into other people's problems.

392
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:51,880
You're always so thoughtful, Chloe.

393
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:56,350
But if you need to talk about it,
go ahead.

394
00:26:57,790 --> 00:26:58,960
I'll at least listen.

395
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:07,230
Things are about
to get hectic for me.

396
00:27:08,730 --> 00:27:11,700
I need you to keep
the business running strong...

397
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:16,970
so the bio division we've secured
doesn't fall apart.

398
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:30,520
Thanks to you,
I was able to get some fresh air.

399
00:27:30,990 --> 00:27:32,090
I'll get going then.

400
00:27:49,870 --> 00:27:50,870
Yes, it's me.

401
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:55,650
I think something's going on
with President Kim Myung Hui.

402
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:57,050
Can you look into it?

403
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:06,520
(Bongmyeong Neighborhood Coffee)

404
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:11,630
Not so fast.

405
00:28:12,330 --> 00:28:13,960
I knew it.

406
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:16,600
So much for insisting I was wrong.

407
00:28:16,970 --> 00:28:19,670
Now you're here at dawn,
checking her out.

408
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:23,770
I wasn't checking her out.
I was just...

409
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:26,180
Just what? What?

410
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:30,650
It was just... Just...

411
00:28:30,650 --> 00:28:32,950
I'll tell you this again.

412
00:28:32,950 --> 00:28:34,620
You and my sister? Not a chance.

413
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:35,690
No!

414
00:28:38,390 --> 00:28:40,390
What on earth are you thinking?

415
00:28:40,490 --> 00:28:43,730
It's not what you think.
I was just worried about you.

416
00:28:44,390 --> 00:28:45,400
Wait a minute.

417
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:48,360
Are you saying you want
to give it a try with him?

418
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:55,610
Yoon Jung!

419
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:02,010
(Adele Group President Kim Myung Hui
to Hold Press Conference)

420
00:29:08,550 --> 00:29:09,550
What?

421
00:29:09,890 --> 00:29:12,320
Myung Hui is personally holding
a press event?

422
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:15,430
All she had to do
was sign the report, so why?

423
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:17,790
Isn't it obvious?

424
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:22,070
She's refusing to simply do
as she's told.

425
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:27,040
She's calling in reporters
so you can't pull any strings,

426
00:29:27,070 --> 00:29:29,210
and she's going to declare
the gems are real.

427
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:32,040
See? I told you not to trust her.

428
00:29:32,910 --> 00:29:35,150
She's proud, full of herself,
and self-righteous.

429
00:29:35,450 --> 00:29:38,050
Did you think she'd choose you
over her own reputation?

430
00:29:38,450 --> 00:29:39,950
Where's the press conference?

431
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,250
At the Adele Gallery, sir.

432
00:29:41,650 --> 00:29:42,750
Let's go. Now.

433
00:29:43,190 --> 00:29:44,290
I'm coming with you.

434
00:29:49,230 --> 00:29:52,260
President Kim Myung Hui is holding
a press conference at the gallery?

435
00:29:53,630 --> 00:29:55,900
I mean,
appraising gems is part of her job.

436
00:29:57,430 --> 00:29:59,940
But Secretary Jung's reaction
didn't seem right.

437
00:30:00,670 --> 00:30:03,340
She rushed out like something bad
had happened to President Kim.

438
00:30:03,910 --> 00:30:06,140
Didn't you ask me to look into her
because something felt off?

439
00:30:08,510 --> 00:30:10,680
Okay. I'll find out what's going on.

440
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:32,040
Hold on a second.

441
00:30:36,740 --> 00:30:39,880
Your mother, I mean President Kim,

442
00:30:40,610 --> 00:30:41,950
do you know
she's holding a press conference?

443
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:44,810
A press conference?

444
00:30:50,990 --> 00:30:53,290
Something's not right here.

445
00:31:08,070 --> 00:31:09,510
(Adele)

446
00:31:23,390 --> 00:31:25,720
We are gathered here today...

447
00:31:26,190 --> 00:31:28,190
to confirm the authenticity
of the ornament...

448
00:31:28,890 --> 00:31:32,600
scheduled for exhibition
at the Adele Gallery.

449
00:31:34,700 --> 00:31:36,870
As an international gemologist,

450
00:31:37,530 --> 00:31:41,470
I state that my evaluation is based
solely on objective facts.

451
00:31:44,940 --> 00:31:46,980
I will now share the results.

452
00:31:47,180 --> 00:31:48,780
No, wait. Hold on a second.

453
00:31:48,780 --> 00:31:50,010
The results are clear.

454
00:31:53,050 --> 00:31:54,420
The gems in this ornament...

455
00:31:57,950 --> 00:32:00,160
are not genuine.

456
00:32:00,890 --> 00:32:01,960
Are they really fake?

457
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,190
Are you sure about the appraisal?

458
00:32:03,190 --> 00:32:05,260
What does this mean for its status
as a cultural asset?

459
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:07,100
Are these results accurate?

460
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:10,570
Are you certain
about your appraisal?

461
00:32:10,870 --> 00:32:12,070
Please comment.

462
00:32:12,770 --> 00:32:14,670
Will the exhibition proceed
as planned?

463
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:16,710
Please give us a comment.

464
00:32:17,340 --> 00:32:18,570
Is this true?

465
00:32:50,310 --> 00:32:53,280
(Pearl in Red)

466
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:56,150
We need more leverage
on Park Tae Ho.

467
00:32:56,150 --> 00:32:58,110
Just one isn't enough.

468
00:32:58,180 --> 00:32:59,520
Get as much as you can.

469
00:32:59,850 --> 00:33:00,980
What are you talking about?

470
00:33:00,980 --> 00:33:03,320
President Kim's been arrested.

471
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:05,720
President Kim was arrested?

472
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:06,920
On what charges?

473
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:09,260
Driven by her grudge
against Jung Ran,

474
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,760
she's promising
to be completely loyal to me.

475
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:15,500
I just need to tame her
and put her to good use.

476
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:18,230
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
